headline: Italy's Intesa partners with BlackRock in private banking in Benelux
summary: Italy's largest bank Intesa Sanpaolo said it would partner with BlackRock, the world's biggest asset manager and a leading Intesa shareholder, to offer digital wealth management services to clients in Belgium and Luxembourg.  "This agreement is a perfect fit with our strategy based on the growth of our wealth management business and the development of new digital solutions," CEO Carlo Messina said.  It launched last year Fideuram Direct, a digital private banking channel to serve younger customers leveraging technology to compete in a sector where players are increasingly betting on scale to lower costs.
